cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper proposes a deep fully convolutional neural network architecture for automated cardiac segmentation from magnetic resonance imaging datasets. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of a neural network for segmentation also involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper discusses the efficiency and scalability of the proposed method, which could be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) applications.
